content:
See the improved recommendations from Decision Optimization on record pages in Salesforce.

When a Decision Optimization is selected as the prediction source of the Einstein Prediction component:

It shows a prediction and top predictors.
The suggested improvements show optimized recommendations, subject to business objective, constraints, conditions, and filters configured in the optimization.
A shaded box is added to the suggested improvements, showing:
A statement describing the combined impact of all suggested improvements.
The new predicted outcome value.
The percent change.
The optimization objective predicted outcome value.

With Decision Optimization, the impact of suggested improvements can be considered together. The optimization provides a new summation statement that describes the predicted outcome when all suggested improvements are combined.

Hereâ€™s an example record with two recommendations:

Fleet management is predicted to decrease the win probability by 1.49%.
Driver development is predicted to increase the win probability by 20.38%.

Together, the recommendations are predicted to increase the win probability to a nearly perfect likelihood to win of 97.79%. The combined impact is 23.49%, with a percent change of 32% compared to the current win probability.

The optimization objective of Stage times Price is predicted to be $55,965,319.33.
title: Using Decision Optimization in Salesforce Predictions
